# tkv2 — component scopes (instance-scoped signal names)

Slice `tkv2-components` of `specs/ssc-toolkit-v2.md`: a reusable widget
function gets instance-scoped signals via `component`/`Ctx` instead of
colliding module-global names.

[Ctx, component, childCtx, ctxClean, ctxName, ctxSignal](std/ui/component.ssc)

```scalascript
// Instance scoping: same component, different keys → distinct names;
// same key → the same (stable) name.
def counterName(key: String): String =
  component("counter", key)(ctx => ctxName(ctx, "count"))

println(counterName("a"))
println(counterName("b"))
println(counterName("a") == counterName("a"))
println(counterName("a") == counterName("b"))

// Ids stay valid JS identifiers: non-[A-Za-z0-9_] chars sanitize to '_'
// (signal ids feed React useState variable names — emitter contract).
println(counterName("pit-28/2026"))

// Signals created through a Ctx are real signals reading their own defaults.
val sigA = component("card", "a")(ctx => ctxSignal(ctx, "expanded", false))
val sigB = component("card", "b")(ctx => ctxSignal(ctx, "expanded", true))
println(sigA())
println(sigB())

// The generic wrapper passes String and Int defaults through.
val draft = component("form", "f1")(ctx => ctxSignal(ctx, "draft", "hello"))
val tick  = component("form", "f1")(ctx => ctxSignal(ctx, "tick", 0))
println(draft())
println(tick())

// Nesting: childCtx prefixes compose parent → child.
val nested = component("page", "home")(ctx => {
  val row = childCtx(ctx, "row", "42")
  ctxName(row, "open")
})
println(nested)
```
